review_blob: on tap at a local resturant. Clear amber colour, tall, fluffy, off-white head. Promising aroma of roasetd malts. Full-bodied, malty with dark hints of roasted malts and bitter chocolate. Earthy hops round it off. Smooth and pleasant carbonation. A pity they dont bottle it.

bottle from local shops. Clear pale golden yellow with a mid-sized white head. Shy but pleasant hoppy nose. Light-bodied, elegant malty background. Good aromatic and bitter hops there, shy and inoffensive but quite pleasant. A "quiet" Pils, perhaps a tad shy - nevertheless quite pleasing.

bottle from a local Getrnkemarkt. Cloudy golden with a tall and cdreamy white head. Wheaty and malty with an intensive yeasty-fruity character. Bold yet well balanced. A very pleasant and smooth Hefeweizen.
bottle from Getrnke Fleischmann Wrth/Isar. Golden brown with a mid-sized beige head. Malty with dark malts and some caramel, also dried fruit. Smooth palate.
bottle from Bierzwerg. Golden with a mid-sized white head. Malty with fruity hints and a touch of vanilla and honey.
bottle from getrnke Flsichmann Wrth/Isar. Dark brown with a beige head. Malty with hints of dried fruit and some chocolate. Smooth palate.

bottle from getrnke Fleischmann Wrth/Isar. Brown colour with a small beige head. Roasty nose. Malty, rosaty hints, also some caramel and a touch of burnt malts. Raisins and some shy dates, plus some caramel and dark chocolate. Complex, smooth and delightful.
bottle from Getrnke Fleischmann Wrth/Isar. Golden with a mid-sizec white head. Malty nose. Malty start, slightly sweet with shy but pleasant hoppy flavours and a lingering bitter-sweet finish.

bottle from Getrnke Fleischmann Wrth/Isar. Golden colour, mid-sized white head. Hoppy-sweet nose. Medium-bodied, malty base with sweet hints, lingering bitter finish. The hoppy character is not as pronounced as I would have expected it to be with a dry-hopped beer, nevertheless a solid and good Heller Bock.

bottle from Getrnke Fleischmann, Wrth/Isar.Cloudy golden with atall white head. Lovely and intense pink grapefruit aroma. Light- to medium-bodied, wheaty with lots of aromatic hops. More pink grapefruit here. Good.
bottle, Merkur Vienna-Htteldorf. Clear amber with a small white head. Malty nose with caramel. Light-bodied, malty background with hints of caramel and biscuits, shy woody hops.

bottle, from local Kaufland. Murky golden with a fluffy white head. Yeasty-fruity nose. Light-bodied, shy but good malty background, shy but nice hops that have a citrusy touch and a pleasantly bitter finish. Fruity yeasty character present throughout. Mild, with typical Zwickelbier characteristics.

bottle, Gru nach Bochum! Clear deep golden yellow with a small white head. Promising fruity hoppy nose. Medium-bodied, good malty base delivering delicious fruity hops, hints of kiwi, ananas and some citrusy hints. The best of both worlds - a classic and solid Helles combined with fancy aromatic hops makes ein groartiges Bier, as the label correctly states.

lhev, erstv z balku od pana doktora - dky moc! Slightly hazy dark chestnut-brown colour with a mid-sized off-white head. Spicy-hoppy nose. Medium- to full-bodied, robust malty base with some dark malts and a shy bitter touch, very faint coffee-like hints. Slightly fruity and very, very spicy. Pleasantly hopped, resiny, slightly grassy with earthy notes. Smooth and velvety on the palate - a very nice little beer.

bottle, many thanks to kappldav123! Slightly hazy golden colour with a tall white head. Good and promising hop aroma. Medium-bodied, good malty background with a hsy grainy touch, lots of aromatic hops, herbal and grassy, also resiny. Well balanced. Delicious stuff!
bottle, many thanks to kappldav123! Hazy amber with a tall beige head. Malty, grainy touch with hints of caramel. pleasantly bitter with a good aromatic hoppy touch. Nice one!
bottle, many thanks to kappldav123! Hazy amber with a tiny head. Sourish nose. Fruity with some caramel and christmasy spices, sour background, quite wild and brett-like.
bottle, many thanks to kappldav123! Amber colour, mid-sized white head. Malty, hints of caramel,shy but pleasant aromatic hops.
bottle, many thanks to kappldav123! Hazy golden with a mid-sized white head. Malty start, quite hoppy from the beginning, herbal accents, spicy and pleasantly bitter.

1l bottle from kappldav123, thanks! Deep golden with a tall white head, good malty nose. Medium-bodied, pleasantly malty with a nice sweet touch of caramel, slightly herbal hops in the finish. Well balanced, well crafted beer.
bottle. Red-brown colour, tiny foamy head. Fruity nose. Cherries, not sweet and not too sour, quite nice!
bottle. Golden with a tiny foamy head. Intensive aroma of marmite. Sour and fruity, not too sour, yeasty with a touch of vegemite. Unusual, quite interesting.

bottle from Heinrichs 3000 Kornwestheim. Hazy golden, tall white head, shy hint of coffee in the nose. Medium-bodied, good malty base, good aromatic hops that add a fruity and floral touch, hints of coffee in the background, also hints of caramel. Unusual and quite nice!
bottle from Heinrichs 3000 Kornwestheim. Golden yellow, white head. Grainy mlaty flavours, cardboardy hops, light-bodied and refreshing.
bottle from Heinrichs 3000 Kornwestheim. Golden yellow, fluff ywhite head, grassy hoppy nose. Light-bodied, malty background with grassy hops, slightly resiny.
bottle from Heinrichs 3000 Kornwestheim. Cloudy yellow, tall head. Wheaty and fruity - light-boded and refreshing.
bottle from Heinrichs 3000 Kornwestheim. Golden with a white head and a fruity nose. Full-bodied, hints of alcohol, fruity hints.
bottle from Heinrichs 3000 Kornwestheim. Amber golden with a mid-sized white head. Malty, shy hints of roasetd malts, shy hoppy touch. Quite mild.
bottle from Heinrichs 3000 Kornwestheim. Cloudy golden yellow, tall and creamy white head. Wheaty and yeasty, not too fruity. Smooth palate.
bottle from Heinrichs 3000 Kornwestheim. Golden yellow with a tall white head and a lovely resiny hop aroma. Medium-bodied, solid malty base, lots of resniy-grassy hops, pleasantly bitter. Delicious.
bottle from Heinrichs 3000 Kornwestheim. hazy deep golden, tall head. Full-bodied, a touch of alcohol is detectable, otherwise full of hoppy goodness, green, fresh and resiny-fruity.
bottle from Heinrichs 3000 Kornwestheim. Cloudy yellow with a creamy head. Wheaty and yeasty with pleasant fruity hints and a cheesy touch.
bottle from Heinrichs 3000 Kornwestheim. Pale yellow, tall white head. Cardboardy hoppy aroma. Shy malty base, some hops with hints of cardboard and dust. Thin and quite boring. Poor Kaiser.
bottle from Heinrichs 3000 Kornwestheim. Golden with a white head. Malty start, shy hoppy touch. Quite thin and boring.
bottle from Heinrichs 3000 Kornwestheim. Golden yellow, small white head. Malty base, grainy, with a dusty hoppy finish.
bottle from Heinrichs 3000 Kornwestheim. Clear golden with a white head. Malty, wheaty and slightly fruity with a dusty hoppy finish.
bottle from Heinrichs 3000 Kornwestheim. Clear golden with a tall white head. Fruity nose. Wheaty with hints of banana and a slightly cardboardy finish.
bottle from Heinrichs 3000 Kornwestheim. Hazy yellow, tall fluffy white head. Yeasty and slightly fruity, quite light but pleasantly wheaty.
bottle from Heinrichs 3000 Kornwestheim. Golden yellow, mid-sized white head. Malty, slightly hoppy with a dusty touch.
bottle from Heinrichs 3000 Kornwestheim. Golden yellow, tall white head. Malty start, grassy-herbal hops, some hay. Low malty sweetness, quite dry. Nice.
bottle from Heinrichs 3000 Kornwestheim. Pale yellow with a tall white head. Resiny nose. Light-bodied, shy but good malty base with a good amount of bitter and aromatic hops, resiny and grassy.

bottle from Heinrichs 3000 Super-Getrnkemarkt Kornwestheim. Clear pale yellow with a fluffy and persistant white head. Grassy hop aroma. Lovely bitter ho flavours from the start, elegant malty base in the background. Grassy and resiny, pleasantly bitter. Excellent!

bottle from Browarium Sklepy Piwne. Golden with a tall white head. Lovely hop aroma, resiny, piney and slightly fruity. Mediujm-bodied, good malty background delivering loads of lovely Sybilla hops. Intensively piney and resiny, with a shy citrusy touch. Smooth and velvety touch. Delicious and very, very moreish.
bottle from Browarium Sklepy Piwne. Golden with a white head and a promising resiny hoppy nose. Medium-bodied, malty with lots of resiny hops, shy fruity touch. Spicy and fragrant, very nice.

bottle from Weinkauff. Clear amber-brown with a creamy off-white head. Chocolatey nose. Medium-bodied, good malty base with a ncie touch of dark honey. Hints of chocolate, caramel and raisins. Quite nice, but I still dont get it why a beer that wants to be from Konstanz is brewed in Bayreuth.

bottle from Henrichs 3000 Supergetrnkemarkt Kornwestheim. Golden colour, fluffy white head, aroma of cinnamon and christmasy spices. Medium- to full-bodied, malty with a pleasant sweetness und lots of spices such as clove, cinnamon and nutmeg.
bottle from Browarium Sklepy Piwne. Slightly hazy broiwnish golden with a small white head. Light-bodied, shy but pleasant malty base, good herbal-grassy hoppy flavours with a shy fruity touch.

bottle from saveur-biere. Slightly hazy deep golden witha tall white head, fluffy, leaving lacework. Hoppy nose. Quite light-bodied for the strength, elegant malty background, herbal-grassy and slightly fruity hops present. Quite high carbonation.
bottle from saveur-biere. Slightly hazy golden colour with a fluffy, persistent white head leaving lacework. Fruity nose. Malty background, herbal-fruity hops, nice Belgian yeast character.
*** Polish beer # 300 *** Hazy golden with a white head. Malty base with good aromatic hops, some tropcial fruits, also a resiny touch. Well balanced.
